{"id":382237,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open_All_Hours","text":"\"Open All Hours\" is a British television sitcom written by Roy Clarke. It was broadcast by the BBC from 1973-1985. It is set in a small grocery shop in Balby, Doncaster, South Yorkshire. It stars Ronnie Barker as the owner Albert Arkwright and David Jason as his nephew Granville, who works for him. Lynda Baron plays nurse Gladys Emanuel, whom Arkwright is strongly attracted to.\nIt was followed in 2013 by \"Still Open All Hours\".","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"United_Kingdom","surface_form":"British","offset":22},{"uri":"Television","surface_form":"television","offset":30},{"uri":"Sitcom","surface_form":"sitcom","offset":41},{"uri":"Roy_Clarke","surface_form":"Roy Clarke","offset":59},{"uri":"Broadcast","surface_form":"broadcast","offset":78},{"uri":"BBC","surface_form":"BBC","offset":95},{"uri":"Grocery","surface_form":"grocery","offset":136},{"uri":"Shop","surface_form":"shop","offset":144},{"uri":"Balby","surface_form":"Balby","offset":152},{"uri":"Doncaster","surface_form":"Doncaster","offset":159},{"uri":"South_Yorkshire","surface_form":"South Yorkshire","offset":170},{"uri":"Ronnie_Barker","surface_form":"Ronnie Barker","offset":196},{"uri":"Owner","surface_form":"owner","offset":217},{"uri":"David_Jason","surface_form":"David Jason","offset":244},{"uri":"Nephew","surface_form":"nephew","offset":263},{"uri":"Lynda_Baron","surface_form":"Lynda Baron","offset":300},{"uri":"Nurse","surface_form":"nurse","offset":318},{"uri":"Still_Open_All_Hours","surface_form":"Still Open All Hours","offset":409}]}